        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 20 at 10:56AM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 1056 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Easton, or near Mason City, moving north at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Easton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
